rComments: Worst prof. Avoid at all cost. His homework on Mobius are awful and some of it is stuff he didn't even teach in class. He thinks we're all mathematicians.

He may not give too many examples but if you did well in high school calculus, you'll be fine. He teaches what you need to know, gives an example or two and moves on. Ask questions, he'll answer helpfully. Don't forget your Mobïus!!

MAT 1730 is no walk in the park, I did well on the first midterm, failed the second and had to work very hard in order to do well on the final. You need to go to class since he write all his notes on the board and his online notes are not always the same as the ones he writes in class.
I don't even know how is he a University professor.

It seems some students have their own problems with this good professor. I don't like his hand writing, but he is super honest, impartial, and moreover he never discriminated. He works hard inside class. Please be fair when you rate this professor.

Overall good prof. The homework is MUCH harder than what you see on exams. Don't know why people are so harsh about the class difficulty! The prof will always post a past exam online and the questions are literally the same but different numbers. Only thing that sucks is his handwriting! But notes are posted online. 9/10 recommend. GO TO THE DGD'S!
Not a very good teacher. Exams are super hard. The best you will like in him : he treats all students equally, without privileging any group of students. Then he deserves AWESOME.

average prof, handwriting got worse as the semester progressed so try and sit in the front if you can. mobs questions are harder than the material learned in class but are great for practice. midterms were basically the same as the practical exams he put on brightspace but the final was a bit harder

He is very smart and courteous. You might not like him only at the beginning. If I see him I would suggest to bring assistant teaching professors to dept of math who can only focus on teaching instead of research.
Very respondent professor. He accepts all questions from students. You can learn a lot in his courses.
Very respectful professor. I learned a lot in his useful course. He solved many examples on board.
Nice professor. He cares all students equally.

I liked him to the fullest because he treats all students equally. It is true his exams are hard, but if you drop by his office he will respond to you very positively. Just go to class and follow his notes then you will do well.

Absolutely terrible prof, the worst one I've had in three years. He may as well be talking to himself during lectures. Can't complete a full sentence without going off on tangents. His writing is complete trash and he makes no effort to make it even slightly legible. His posted notes and solutions aren't any different. Dropped class after 1 month.

The class was tougher than Calculus 2 taken in the Winter Term. He has difficulty seeing which makes it hard to get an answer to a question. He's very entertaining and can make the material seem easy but when doing the homework it is much more difficult and abstract. Barely passed.
This course is time consuming, make sure to make time for it and get help when you need it.

Not an easy class but he does know his material very well. Hard grading but the teacher is teaching a very hard subject. The prof is very nice and if you did well in grade 12 calculus you will be more than fine. Supper smart man. Overall good professor.
the homework is much more difficult than the examples in class. GO TO THE DGD'S AND THE HELP CENTER
Midterms only have the most difficult examples, they're not fair.

Professor Benoit Dionne is a really great professor who knows what he is teaching and makes sure you know what to practice for the tests. His behaviour is hilarious at times which keeps the class a little light. the class is an easy one, just listen and show up to take notes.

Dionne is a decent prof. Unfortunately, his lectures are very boring and it made me hate math so much. Sit in the front because he writes very small on a black board so you can barely see what he's writing. The dgd doesn't help much but i still recommend you go for extra help. It is a very hard class and the average of our class was very low.

In my opinion, the reviews received on this website do not reflect his teaching. Overall, teaches at a decent pace, knowledgeable about the subject he teaches and is very helpful if you see him during office hours. Keeps the class entertaining. Only drawback is that he tends to finish the lectures late.

Hard class, pro doesn't explain really well, do the recommended problems, there's a lot but it's gonna help you and this teacher doesn't give exams from past years so make yourself some friends of other sections or english ones so you can have theirs.

Classes were average in interest. Lots of practice questions. DGD quizes were difficult and worth a large portion of the grade.  Les classes nétaient pas très interressants. Les quiz dans les GDDs étaint difficiles, et valaient beacoup.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lots of homework', 'Test heavy']

rComments: He is not the worst professor but clarity in the class was poor. His handwriting and notes are fairly poor. Sometimes his examples aren't very good.   Class did very poorly on the first midterm, and he claimed adjustments would be made later. Come exam time he said nothing will be changed, and it reflected in the course average (very low).
Not a bad prof, but not awesome neither. He's blind as a bat, so sit in the front row. He often seemed lost in his own course. This class is not made to be easy, so DO HIS RECOMMENDED PROBLEMS!!!
Avoid him if you don't want to fail
His teaching technique is super bad. Avoid
He sucks, he writes stupidly and dosent know how to teach... Dont take him the class average was 55% thank god i got threw with a 8.1
he is one of the worst teacher to be hired at a university.He is always lost by himself.he could probably be acceptable teaching in french,I doubt it,

He's ok in clarity of voice... But when he gives an example, it's only with other variables and that is not what u call AN EXAMPLE!!! Besides that he's ok... This is the weed-out course so it will be hard... And it was

Honestly can be great if he wanted to explain better, but the thing is he gets to class and makes up examples on the spot that he himself cant solve until he brings it home and shows you what he did without explaining exam wasnt hard just long.

Very good prof. He is very clear in what he explains and what he expects, although some of the exams were a challenge. Takes the time to explain things well during office hours. Teaches maths with enthusiasm. A usually boring subject was not so bad! He is also open to suggestions.

Started off hating him but as the year went on i got used to him. Probably cuz math is my least favorite subject. Very smart guy, pretty helpful outside the classroom. His exam questions are based from his "devoirs assignés" and "Problèmes suggérés" DO THEM.

This teacher is very intelligent but to my experience has one of the worst teaching techniques.  His notes are well prepared but he goes threw the lessons to fast and assumes that you know almost every rules, just makes it overwhelming at some point.  To be honest, I wanna pass this class not for the credit but for not having him as a teacher again
he has the worst notes
Super cute comme prof! Toujours disponible pour nous si on en a de besoin! J'ai bien réussi dans le cours en partie à cause du centre-d'aide mais quand même excellent prof!!

Worst prof in the history of math profs. I had him for both my first-year math classes, and I'm sure I would have done better if not for him. He is getting better with the quality of his notes, but I would make sure to attend ALL the DGDs (they help). He asuumes that we know as much as he does when he's teaching, so don't be afraid to ask questions

Quand que d'autre prof de math de l'université t'insulte indirectement dans leur cour... je pense que c'est un signe que tu n'est pas un bon prof. Dionne est horrible, il n'enseigne pas bien la matière, il rit de toi quand tu n'as pas la bonne réponse a sa question, il perd 10 minute a réécire un mot sur son fichu projecteur tablette. etc etc.
La plus pire professeur au monde.
Enseigne pas bien la matière, il prend pour acqui que vous connaissez tout...  Mysère a comprendre ses raisonnement.

His notes, homework corrections and examples in class are full of mistakes. Does not explain well at all. If you can, change sections. The material is not very hard but his method of teaching makes it very challenging to understand the material. He is a very bright individual but not meant to be a teacher. Thats my 2 cent
Naturellement...
HORRIBLE teacher. He can't communicate because he's in his own little world. just brutal.
Terrible, gets confused with what he says. He knows his stuff but can't really communicate it to the students. Although he is very quick to answer the question you send him via email.

He is horrible.He's the type of prof that gives math a bad name.His exams are so much harder than what he actually teaches and he complains when people talk they waste time when he wastes half the class because he gets lost in his own examples.Because of him,I'm on the point of failing calculus.He can't even answer questions
Pretty good class, the teacher just has a very hard time to explain..Gets lost very ofter in his own explanitions
This is the worst teacher in the  whole world... seriously he shouldn't teach

I hate to be so mean, but this professor was the worst. ever.  He did not seem to care about his students one bit.  Granted, it was a huge class, but his teaching style consisted of throwing stuff on the board, drawing potato-like shapes, giving no extra explanations to his notes, and laughing at questions asked by students.
Can you read this? Benoit Dionne sure can't.

He's the worst Math teacher ever! He laughs at your questions and doesn't care about you at all! His exams are on stuff much more harder than we've learn...or on stuff we've never learn! I got a F in his class, and I redid the same course with another teacher and endup with an A...he's the worst teacher ever!
This little man is a horrible prof.  He goes though the material at lightning speed.  Make simple concepts very complex.  Change sections: that's what I did.
the prof is alright but the class is hard :(

He is very high-strung... I thought he would break keyboard at some point ... His course was a nightmare to me ...
Is boring and don't give explanation
